---
entries:
  Material_00:
    - text: Collecting Ingredients
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "There are many more ingredients than those used for cooking food.\nCollect and experiment with different ingredients to make all sorts\nof things!"
  Material_13:
    - text: Luring Fish
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Tossing ingredients that serve as bait near fish in the water will\nattract them. Different bait works on different kinds of fish."
  Material_01:
    - text: Cooking Secrets
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Using more of an effect-imparting ingredient when cooking will\nincrease that effect in the resulting dish."
  Material_14:
    - text: "What's That, Pooch?"
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "If you befriend a dog, it may lead you to something interesting."
  Material_02:
    - text: Monster Ingredients
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "If you combine monster parts dropped by fallen foes in a cooking pot\nwith things like lizards and butterflies, you can create elixirs with\nspecial effects."
  Material_15:
    - text: Ingredient Effects
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Certain ingredients give elixirs or dishes special properties.\nBut don't get greedy: ingredients with different effects will\ncancel each other out."
  Material_03:
    - text: Roasting Ingredients
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Throw ingredients like mushrooms or fish directly into a fire to roast \nthem and up their health benefits. Keep in mind that roasting an\ningredient won't activate its potential special effect."
  Material_16:
    - text: Ingredient Effects
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "You can only enjoy one effect from a dish or elixir at any given time.\nIf you're relying on an active effect, be careful not to cancel it\nby eating something with a new effect."
  Material_04:
    - text: Fairy Effects
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "If you keep a fairy in your pouch, it will automatically restore some\nhearts when you fall in battle."
  Material_05:
    - text: Gems
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "The gems that sometimes drop when you break ore deposits fetch\na high price when sold."
  Weapon_00:
    - text: "Where's the Fire?"
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "When a wooden weapon or shield catches fire, you can extinguish\nit by unequipping the burning item."
  Material_06:
    - text: Cooking Pots
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Cook up some wild cuisine by throwing together some ingredients\nand seeing what happens. You can't cook with an unlit pot."
  Weapon_01:
    - text: Weapon Durability
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Durability varies with every weapon. Always be aware of the condition\nof your equipment. A weapon breaking at the wrong time is never\na good thing."
  Material_07:
    - text: Cutting Grass
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Wildlife taking shelter in the grass will sometimes jump out when you\ncut down their hiding place."
  Weapon_02:
    - text: Throwing Weapons
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "If your weapon is close to breaking, try throwing it at an enemy\nusing "
    - control:
        one:
          type7:
            field_1: 2
            field_2:
              - 21
              - 205
    - text: ". It will double your damage if it hits!"
  Material_08:
    - text: No Stone Unturned
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Wildlife taking shelter under a rock will sometimes jump out when you\nlift up their hiding place."
  Weapon_03:
    - text: Special Bows
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "A few bows fire multiple arrows at once. They offer several times\nthe power of normal bows, while strangely only consuming one\narrow at a time."
  Material_09:
    - text: Octo Balloon
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "When inflated, this sac obtained from defeating Octoroks is\nextremely buoyant. Place one near something you want to lift\nto make it float into the air."
  Weapon_04:
    - text: More Than a Weapon
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Metal weapons create sparks that can be used to light a fire.\nFurthermore, if you set a wooden weapon on fire, it can be\nused as a torch."
  Weapon_06:
    - text: Boomerangs
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Throw a boomerang with "
    - control:
        one:
          type7:
            field_1: 2
            field_2:
              - 21
              - 205
    - text: ", and it will fly in a large arc before\nreturning to you. What goes around comes around!"
  Armor_00:
    - text: Armor Sets
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Wearing the top, bottom, and headwear from the same set can earn\nyou some bonus effects."
  Weapon_07:
    - text: Weapon Bonuses
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Some weapons you'll come across have special properties that set\nthem apart from others of their class, such as superior durability or\nabove-average attack power."
  Weapon_08:
    - text: Critical Hit
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "When using a weapon with this bonus, the last hit in a series of\nattacks will deal double the damage."
  Material_10:
    - text: Fairy Effects
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "If you have a fairy help you cook, the tonic you produce together\nrestores a great deal of hearts."
  Weapon_09:
    - text: Master Sword
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "When your hearts are full, you can fire a beam from the sword\nwith "
    - control:
        one:
          type7:
            field_1: 2
            field_2:
              - 21
              - 205
    - text: ". The more Heart Containers you have, the further the\nbeam's range."
  Material_11:
    - text: Scorching Climates
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "In the extreme heat of volcanic regions, ingredients will cook simply\nby placing them on the ground. Use this to your advantage to\nprepare meals on the go."
  Material_12:
    - text: Freezing Climates
    - control:
        zero:
          type4:
            field_1: 0
    - text: "Some ingredients will freeze if submerged in ice-cold water or when\nleft out in frigid regions. There are a few ingredients that taste\neven better frozen."